title: Infant mortality rate in the Netherlands 2008 to 2018
yAxis: Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 6 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2017 to 2015.
Similarly, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2015 to 2013.
Differently, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2013 to 2011.
Also, the next significant trend is moderately neutral which exists from 2010 to 2008.
Also, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2018 to 2017.
But, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2011 to 2010.
gold: In 2018 , the infant mortality rate in the Netherlands was 3.5 . This means that out of every 1,000 newborns , nearly four died before their first birthday . Infant mortality was lowest in 2015 , when the rate was 3.3 deaths per 1,000 live born children .
